o3 Answer:
To evaluate a binomial coefficient  \(\displaystyle {n\choose r}\) we use the factorial formula  

\[
{n\choose r}= \frac{n!}{r!\,(n-r)!}.
\]

(a)  \(\displaystyle {7 \choose 3}\)

\[
{7\choose3}= \frac{7!}{3!\,4!}
            =\frac{7\cdot6\cdot5\cdot4!}{3!\,4!}
            =\frac{7\cdot6\cdot5}{3\cdot2\cdot1}
            =\frac{210}{6}
            =35.
\]

(b)  \(\displaystyle {11 \choose 4}\)

\[
{11\choose4}= \frac{11!}{4!\,7!}
             =\frac{11\cdot10\cdot9\cdot8\cdot7!}{4!\,7!}
             =\frac{11\cdot10\cdot9\cdot8}{4\cdot3\cdot2\cdot1}
             =\frac{7920}{24}
             =330.
\]

Answers:  
(a) 35  
(b) 330

